node.text:
New artwork in my houseplant series. This one was a vote on combo of the peacock calathea and the south American Margay. This is the August artwork. 
I have a baby peacock calathea. It's very tiny but does push up a new leaf every week or so.

node.text:
Kintsugi, Lemonade and Henpeito pins are restocked now on my online store! 
Because of new customs regulations in EU, right now I would recommend European Union customers to use my Etsy store instead right now. Their higher selling fees means things are little more expensive there so I created code HELPAMEU to bring down the price a little more inline with my own stores pricing. This will help you avoid high custom fees you will encounter otherwise. Everyone else please use my normal shop front. 
#enamelpin

node.text:
I bet many people don't remember this one. I started this waaaay back in 2016 and made one WIP post and then... Lost interest. At some point a long time ago I packed up a bunch of unfinished original artworks to @nullight and I was super surprised a few days ago to see it finished on my feed 😂
Kila did a fantastic job of finishing this one, completing the mane and refining details.
(I wonder what other pictures she may be working on in secret 😈)

#traditionalart #traditionalartist #colorpencil #pencilart #pencildrawing  #fabercastell #polychromospencils #carandache #luminencepencils #traditionalartist  #pencildrawing #lion

node.text:
I am happy to announce that both my shop is reopened now, and shiny new things have been added! Like the kintsugi dangle pin and cloudy lemonade shaker charms. Do you have a particular favourite? (My fav is the henpeitō pin, modelled after my own sweet round Orpington hens).
Go to www.sushiartstudio.com or follow the link in my profile. Worldwide shipping
